24/09/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The regular meeting of the political directors of the Steering Board of the Peace Implementation Council (PIC) opened Thursday (23 September) in Sarajevo. According to Office of the High Representative spokeswoman Ljiljana Radetic, the meeting will focus on progress in implementing reforms aimed at enabling BiH to join NATO's Partnership for Peace (PfP) programme, as well on the 16 steps laid out in the European Commission's Feasibility Study. The PIC will also come up with a recommendation on how to complete other reforms by the end of the year, enabling the country to join PfP and start negotiations on a Stability and Association Agreement with the EU next year. (FENA, OHR press release - 23/09/04) 
